The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 25: Unitech has reduced its workforce of 1,700 employees by about 10 per cent as part of a cost-cutting measure. Apart from downsizing employee strength over the last four to five months, the company is not filling up vacancies that were created by normal attrition.          
	 quot;Our normal attrition is there. Naturally we are not looking for replacements, Unitech chairman Ramesh Chandra said.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 25: Industry associations such as Ficci, the CII and Assocham will not have to pay any tax on their income if their activities benefit members only. However, if an industry body extends services to non-members, it will come under the tax net, an official said.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 25: Executives of public sector oil firms will go on strike from work indefinitely from January 7 against the minuscule wage hikes approved by the government. The strike may cripple fuel supplies and do irreparable damage to oilwells.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 25: Companies that have resorted to overseas borrowing to raise capital are likely to see an erosion in their balance sheets in the current fiscal because of the rupee depreciation and drop in stock prices, a Credit Suisse report said.                            
	 Calcutta, Dec. 25: Lookad was selected the best advertising agency at the Sunday Indian and IIPM Regional Excellence Awards function.
                                                                                                                         
